HEADWORD: outpour
<hw>out"pour`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A flowing out; a free
discharge.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An effusion (of sentiment or emotion;
